<concept id="blackbery_bbm_platform" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>BBM Platform</title>
    <shortdesc><i>The BBM Social Platform (BBMSP) provides APIs that allow you to leverage the social features and functionality of BlackBerry Messenger from within your app.</i></shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <title>Installation:</title>
            <p>To use this API in your project, add the BBM plugin:</p>
            <p><pre scale="80">webworks plugin add com.blackberry.bbm.platform</pre></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Learning Resources:</title>
            <p><xref format="html" href="https://developer.blackberry.com/devzone/blackberryworld/bbm/" scope="external">Download BBM SDK Resources</xref>Download the resources required to use the BBM SDK for WebWorks [BlackBerry].</p>
            <p><xref format="html" href="https://developer.blackberry.com/html5/documentation/bbm_social_platform_ww.html" scope="external">Getting Started Guide</xref>Setup the BBM SDK for BlackBerry WebWorks [BlackBerry Developer Resource Center].</p>
            <p><xref format="html" href="https://github.com/blackberry/BB10-WebWorks-Samples/tree/WebWorks-2.0/bbm" scope="external">Sample - BBM for BB10</xref>Sample that demonstrates how to use the BlackBerry BBM APIs for BlackBerry 10 [BlackBerry on GitHub].</p>
            <p><xref format="html" href="http://devblog.blackberry.com/2012/11/blackberry-webworks-bbm-integration/" scope="external">Tutorial - WebWorks app and BBM</xref></p>
        </section>
